<TITLE> Court defers charge-framing against Loby </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, June 3 (bdnews24.com) -- A special court Sunday deferred the date for framing charges against former BNP lawmaker Ali Asgar Loby in a Tk 17.23 crore tax-dodging case. Judge Shahed Nur Uddin of the Special Judge's Court-3 fixed June 5 for framing the charges in the case, filed by the National Board of Revenue. Loby's lawyers appealed to court to defer the date as they said they did not get an attested copy of the case. NBR's deputy commissioner for tax Mohammad Nurul Amin filed the case with Dhaka Metropolitan Senior Special Judge's Court on May 23. Joint forces detained Bangladesh Cricket Board ex-president Loby at his Gulshan home on Feb 6. bdnews24.c
